1. *Naopako* sam obukao majicu jer mi je bilo toplo. (I put on my shirt *backwards* because I was hot.)
2. Vozio je *naopako* bicikl, ali je uspeo da stigne do cilja. (He rode his bike *upside down*, but he managed to reach the finish line.)
3. Sve ide *naopako* od kada je otvorio novu firmu. (Everything is going *wrong* since he opened his new company.)
4. *Naopako* je okrenuo ključ u bravici i nije mogao da otvori vrata. (He turned the key *the wrong way* in the lock and couldn't open the door.)
5. Čini mi se da gledaš svet *naopako*. (It seems to me that you see the world *backwards*.)
6. U redu su raspoređene knjige, ali ova stoji *naopako*. (The books are arranged properly, but this one is standing *upside down*.)
7. Kada se prevrneš *naopako* u bazenu, svet izgleda potpuno drugačije. (When you flip *upside down* in the pool, the world looks completely different.)
8. Treba da okrenete čitav sistem *naopako* ako želite da rešite problem. (You need to turn the whole system *upside down* if you want to solve the problem.)
9. Deca vole da se igraju i hodaju *naopako*. (Children love to play and walk *backwards*.)
10. Kada je došao u novu zemlju, morao je da uči jezik *naopako*. (When he came to a new country, he had to learn the language *backwards*.)